cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a new operator for feature upsampling in convolutional networks, which is critical for dense prediction tasks such as object detection and semantic/instance segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also emphasizes the lightweight and fast computation of the proposed operator, which suggests a possible fit for categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper introduces a new approach for content-aware handling, which could be relevant to categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
